\prod_{k=1}^n 1-{1\over 2^k} = {1\over2}\left(\prod_{k=1}^{n-1} 1-{1\over2} \left({1\over2}\right)^k\right) = {1\over2}\left ( \prod_{k=1}^{n-1}1-2^{-k-1} \right) \implies
\prod_{k=1}^\infty 1-{1\over 2^k} = {1\over2}\left (\prod_{k=1}^{\infty}1-2^{-k-1} \right)
